description: Route AI work by task complexity and verify all generated trading output
alwaysApply: true
---

# Model routing

- Treat model names, availability, pricing, usage limits, and routing as changeable product configuration.
- Prefer the currently available model appropriate to the task. Use Auto for routine work unless explicit model control is materially useful.
- Reserve frontier reasoning models for architecture, security, high-risk decisions, and hard disagreements. Use fast workhorse models for bounded edits, extraction, formatting, and repetitive test generation.
- Enable Max Mode only when the larger context window materially helps.
- Discover API model identifiers at runtime; do not assume IDE display names are valid API identifiers.
- Do not claim or infer Auto's underlying model.

# Repository safeguards

- Keep Elliott Wave rules, risk calculations, price levels, and confidence adjustments deterministic and covered by tests.
- Use LLM output as advisory input only. Validate it against schemas, preserve an audit trail, and retain an honest abstention path.
- Minimise prompts and personal data. Never include credentials, account identifiers, or unnecessary raw payloads in model calls or logs.
- Run focused tests for changed modules, then the full test suite for routing, risk, execution, or schema changes.
- For Inline Edit, provide all selection-specific context in the prompt. Use Agent with explicit context for multi-file or conversation-dependent work.
